 :tx/rationale "Create task: CRB-8: cass-as-extractor for cross-session reconciliation. When braid observe runs CRB reconciliation, ALSO query cass search with the observation text (via shell invocation of cass search --robot --json). If cass returns matches from prior sessions, display them as [history] results alongside [spec]/[task]/[observation] results. This closes the final reconciliation gap: store has project-specific knowledge, cass has cross-project cross-session knowledge. An agent can never complain about a 'new' problem that was solved in a prior session. BACKGROUND: Session 026 dog-food assessment complained about issues discussed 6+ times in prior sessions per cass search. CRB-7 broadens scan within the store. CRB-8 extends beyond the store to session history. Together they check ALL knowledge sources. CONSTRAINT: cass invocation must be --robot --json --limit 3. Timeout 2s. Failure is silent (cass unavailable = no history results, not an error). TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-024, ADR-FOUNDATION-007. ACCEPTANCE: (A) observe about 'task list truncation' shows [history] results from prior sessions. (B) cass timeout → no error, just no history section. (C) cass not installed → graceful degradation. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs"
